14/03/2006
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The political directors of the Peace Implementation Council's board for BiH will meet in Vienna on Wednesday (15 March), according to an announcement from the Office of the High Representative. 
This will be the first meeting chaired by the new top international envoy in BiH, Christian Schwarz-Schilling. 
On Thursday, he is expected to make his first address to the OSCE Permanent Council, also in Vienna.
In other news, a delegation from the Finnish Parliament is visiting Sarajevo this week. 
Finland assumes the rotating EU presidency in July. 
(Dnevni avaz - 14/03/06; NTV Hayat, OSCE Web site, Fena, PBS BiH - 13/03/06)
